    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 43</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 140</em></p>\n<h3>Statistics</h3>\n<p><strong>Cost</strong> 7,000 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 15 lbs.</p>\n<p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> 20 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> B and P; <strong>Special</strong> scatter</p>\n<p><strong>Misfire</strong> 1-2; <strong>Capacity</strong> 2</p>\n<p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p>\n<h3>Description</h3>\n<p>This twin-barreled shotgun can be shot one barrel at a time, or both together as one attack. A double shot that fires bullets is inaccurate, and takes a -4 penalty on both attacks.</p>\n<p>A double shot that fires bullets targets only a single creature and increases the damage of each barrel to 2d6 points (Small) or 2d8 points (Medium) for a total of 4d6 or 4d8 points of damage. A doublebarreled shotgun uses metal cartridges (loaded with either a bullet or pellets) as ammunition.</p>\n<p><strong>This is an advanced firearm.</strong></p>"
